<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF91FFED39D30A6445B7B947" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF91FFED39D30A644214B96B" blockId="31.[136,1452,338,1120]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED39D30A644626BA43" bold="true" box="[136,264,338,364]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Subshrubs</emphasis>
<quantity id="640843B7FF91FFED384D0A6446A3BA42" box="[278,397,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" unit="cm" value="37.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="25.0">25–50 cm</quantity>
tall, usually cespitose, bearing a well-developed, woody underground root-like system. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED39D30A4047F4BABF" bold="true" box="[136,218,374,400]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Leaves</emphasis>
with (2–)3–5(–7) pairs of pinnae; (4–)6–8(–13) pairs of leaflets; rachis nectaries (1)2–3, patelliform to rarely verruciform; blade subcoriaceous to coriaceous, margin glabrous, leaflets (0.8–)1.2–2(–3.5) cm, discolor, glabrous on both surfaces, sometimes sparsely pubescent on the lower surface near the insertion of the secondary petiolule, unilateral tuft of trichomes on the lower surface absent. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED3BA00AD4448ABAD3" bold="true" box="[763,932,482,508]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Inflorescences</emphasis>
of simple thyrsi, cymulae of usually geminate spikes, sometimes 3–4 ternate, vinaceous. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED3B36093045E2B90F" bold="true" box="[621,716,518,544]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Flowers</emphasis>
monoclinous, vinaceous to reddish. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED3D3409304383B90F" bold="true" box="[1135,1197,518,544]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Fruit</emphasis>
a follicule, straight to very rarely slightly curved, flat-compressed, 5.5–6.5 × 
<quantity id="640843B7FF91FFED3BB2091C447BB96A" box="[745,853,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" unit="cm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 cm</quantity>
, valves vinaceous to dark-brown (
<figureCitation id="3BCBF2D7FF91FFED3D8F091C4203B96B" box="[1236,1325,554,580]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="9.[136,229,1992,2014]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,190,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,190,1968]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 2. Subshrub species of Stryphnodendron. A. Stryphnodendron heringeri Occhioni f.; B. Stryphnodendron barbatulum Rizzini &amp; Heringer; C. Stryphnodendron platyspicum Rizzini &amp; Heringer; D. &amp; E. Stryphnodendron cristalinae Heringer, the woody underground root-like system in detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520284/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF91FFED39E6097845B7B947" blockId="31.[136,1452,338,1120]" box="[189,665,590,617]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED39E60978468EB947" bold="true" box="[189,416,590,616]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Vernacular names:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED38E7097845B7B947" box="[444,665,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Barbatimão-miúdo.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF91FFED39E609444251B8A6" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF91FFED39E6094446D7B9D6" blockId="31.[136,1452,338,1120]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED39E6094446DEB9A3" bold="true" box="[189,496,626,652]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF91FFED3B5709444471B9A3" authorityName="Rizzini &amp; Heringer" authorityYear="1966" box="[524,863,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyspicum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED3B5709444471B9A3" box="[524,863,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Stryphnodendron platyspicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
samples are known only from the 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF91FFED3DA209444285B9A3" box="[1273,1451,626,652]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Federal District</collectingRegion>
and neighboring areas in 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF91FFED38F809A04530B99E" box="[419,542,662,689]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FF91FFED3B1809A045A5B99F" box="[579,651,662,688]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The natural habitats of this species are very reduced, mainly due to the urban expansion in Brasília and surroundings. This species is usually found in woody cerrados, but also in more open physiognomies (campo cerrado).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF91FFED39E608344251B8A6" blockId="31.[136,1452,338,1120]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED39E608344649B833" bold="true" box="[189,359,770,796]" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Conservation:</emphasis>
—Vulnerable (VU B1ab(i,iii)+2ab(ii,iii) [AOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FF91FFED3ACC08344339B833" box="[919,1047,770,796]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" unit="km" value="60.0">60.000 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFF91FFED3D4C08344331B83F" attach="left" box="[1047,1055,770,784]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">2</superScript>
, EOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FF91FFED3D2708344230B833" box="[1148,1310,770,796]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3338389999999998" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" unit="km" value="2333.839">2,333.839 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFF91FFED3C4508344208B83F" attach="left" box="[1310,1318,770,784]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">2</superScript>
]. Although some populations of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF91FFED383608104595B86F" authorityName="Rizzini &amp; Heringer" authorityYear="1966" box="[365,699,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyspicum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED383608104595B86F" box="[365,699,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">Stryphnodendron platyspicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to small areas, 
<emphasis id="91843240FF91FFED3AA208114312B86F" box="[1017,1084,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="258">in situ</emphasis>
observations in Brasília revealed that they are usually abundant in individuals. Furthermore, herbarium collections indicate that the species is frequently found in conservation units, such as the Águas Emendadas Biological Reserve and the IBGE Ecological Reserve.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF91FFED39E608A4447CB8FF" pageId="31" pageNumber="258" type="description">
